<br>
*disclaimer* I am not a complete ass, I have only used this twice, once on a twink Vah Shir warrior in DL, and once on a ranger in KC who insisted he could tank the adds.  I believe the ranger's exact comment was &quot;Just sit and buff, I'll handle CC&quot;*end disclaimer*<br>
<br>
What I do is to pull out my chanter rules macro and spam the group for a few fights (c'mon, we all have or have had these in our carreers), then I spend the next few fights saying exactly how many times I had to mezz EACH mob (i.e. Mezzed a drachnid webmaster twice, still moving, mezzed a Drolvarg rager twice, still moving, medding).  This only happens for 2 fights before I get tired of typing.   By this time, I am pretty certain which moron is breaking mezz constantly.  He then gets the aggro buff cycled onto him.  Period.  The effect of this is that ALL unmezzed mobs turn on them and start hitting. <br>
<br>
This is of course more effective for rogues/monks/rangers that refuse to assist (although rogues seem to be really good at assisting <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ), but tanks seem to learn after one or two close calls (or deaths, for that matter, most clerics I group with agree with this tactic)<br>
<br>
Later<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
