<br>
I was down in Chardok with some very capable, trusted friends.  We decided to take a ranger up on his /ooc for a group, just to have a rounded group and give the guy a break coz he'd been /shouting for a while.  Little did we know what an adventure this would turn out to be!<br>
<br>
We go down fairly deep.  Well we WERE going down to near Herbalist, but stopped at the bridge because the ranger was acting silly and making all sorts of n00b mistakes -- the MAJOR one being he was breaking mezzes.  At first I was like, &quot;Hey uberd00d_001, use /assist hon, and we'll stay alive easier.&quot;  Totally and completely ignored, I was.  Getting irritated, I was.  /tell to leader, &quot;You see this n00b breaking mezzes?!  What level did he say he was?&quot; as the bard tells me &quot;You noticed how that ranger is ninja-looting?&quot; Before I get/give a response a Sarnak Battle Shield drops.  Uberdud says to us so when are we going to roll on that, I can really use it.  ?!?  The leader tells him that we'll roll at the end, like we were for the other things that dropped.  <br>
<br>
Once again, in a multiple mob fight, I can't seem to keep the mobs mezzed.  Getting angry at the waste of mana (thank Mithanial Marr for ToT and Wandering Mind) I tell the guy in group, &quot;Look uberdud, use your /assist key!!!!!  You're making my job harder than it needs to be&quot;  Ready for this?  He says, &quot;Look princess, I have a 60 enchanter, I know what you're supposed to do, why don't you just charm them so I can hit them&quot; THEN he says, &quot;What's an /assist key?&quot; OMG OMG OMG<br>
<br>
Groupmember 1:  ??<br>
Groupmember2:  What did you just say?!?<br>
Groupmember3:  You don't have an assist key?<br>
Groupmember4: !! You have a chanter?  He live long in groups?<br>
Uberdud:  Tell me how to make one and I'll do it.<br>
Me:  Hello?! WHAT level did you say you are?<br>
Uberdud:  And while we're not pulling mobs, let's roll on that gear.  I really need gear.  (It's true, I looked at his gear after he looked at mine--was some nice stuff but most wasn't).<br>
<br>
We proceed to tell him how to make/use an assist key.  We proceed to go ahead and /random for the drops.  The cleric says he would seed and rolls a 768.  We start rolling.  The ranger /ran 0 - 100.  He gets told that 768 is seed.  He /ran 101.  ??? <br>
<br>
Cleric:  Dude, random is 768.<br>
Me:  SWEET!  (OK bad reference to a movie, but I couldn't help myself.)<br>
Member3:  Um are you for real?<br>
<br>
He finally got the idea, and by this time we had pops in room, so we started fighting.  This guy starts spamming us with &quot;What did I win?  Aren't we gonna finish rolling?  Why are you killing mobs now? We're doing something important here.&quot;  I held my breath because I KNOW two of the group members and they're about to get medieval on this guy's buttocks.  Sure enough -- <br>
<br>
Well, I'll spare you the gory details, but it was not a pretty sight.  The guy saying a huff saying that we deliberately held out loot, wouldn't give him his choice even though he was 4th in line, said he knew how to play a ranger even if he didn't know the subleties of the game like /assist, and said I was a crappy chanter if I couldn't mezz mobs that he would accidentally hit.  I was repeating, as was the bard during this, &quot;But what did *I* win?!?!&quot; throughout the  whole thing.  <br>
<br>
We all started laughing at this guy coz what else could ya do?  If you get angry you lose the fun.  We picked the wrong chocolate out of the box.  Life is just like that some times.  You just have to spit it out, put the uneaten part back so others can see what they're missing, and hurry for the nearest exit.   <br>
